profile_positions.description:
•	Responsible for the safety and security of the designated United Nations Official/s to whom he/she is assigned during the tour of duty; 
•	Conduct all Close Protection security operations as outlined in the reference 
•	Coordinate all activities with relevant parties to include the appropriate security organizations as required; 
•	Always remain within the proximity of the Protectee(s) or other duties as directed by the TCO/CP TL including but not limited to motorcade driving, security advance, surveillance detection, movement tracking and/or counter assault;  
•	Conducting mandatory UN refresher courses to maintain our awareness in the field. IED, First Aid.
•	Liaises with relevant civil police, military, law enforcement and other officials as necessary.
•	Supervising the drivers in the performance of their assigned duties; 
•	Operating all personal protection equipment and assure equipment readiness; 
•	Carry all issued equipment while on duty including body armour where required; 
•	Excellent standard of punctuality and dependability of attendance; • Work efficiently with other colleagues of the CPU to achieve unit goals.  
•	Updates the Team Leader on a continuous basis of all movements and unusual incidents involving the principal(s);
•	Behaving in a professional manner always with our Principals 
•	I perform any other duty as assign by the Close Protection Team Leader, Close Protection Coordinator, Chief SIOC, CSO and/or PSA. 
•	I report any adverse effects of physical, mental, emotional and personal problems those may adversely affect my job performance. 
•	Hold a valid Close Protection Officer pistol and shoulder fired firearm qualification. 
•	I hold a valid Emergency Trauma Bag (ETB) First Responder certification. 
•	I hold a valid UN Driving Permit. 
•	Meet and maintain the physical fitness standards set in the revised close protection officer course curriculum and guidance on UN protective services and training materials.
